18/06/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Deputy Foreign Minister Bogdan Aurescu announced on Thursday (June 17th) that Bucharest and Washington have begun talks on deploying elements of the proposed US missile shield in Romania.
US Undersecretary of State for Arms Control and International Security Affairs Ellen Tauscher confirmed in Bucharest that she and her delegation would hold "consultations ...
on security issues of mutual interest", including the missile defence shield.
Romania was officially invited to join project in February.
It would host medium-range ballistic missile interceptors that would become operational by 2015.
(AFP, Hotnews.ro, Evenimentul Zilei - 17/06/10)
